Episodes.Title: Call a Clambulance!
Episodes.Plot: Oona's friend Avi broke a bone in his tail and has gone to see a doctor. The Bubble Guppies aren't too worried--after all, it's a doctor's job to make Avi feel better. Everybody say "Ahhhh!"

Episodes.Title: The Crayon Prix!
Episodes.Plot: Green means GO! The Bubble Guppies are racing their quick, colorful cars for the ultimate prize--a big box of crayons! Take the wheel and help the racers mix colors, make new shades, and speed across the finish line!

Episodes.Title: Bubble Puppy!
Episodes.Plot: Sit! Stay! Fetch! Gil wants to adopt a puppy! But the Bubble Guppies have to learn how to take care of a pet before he can bring the little guy home.

Episodes.Title: Build Me a Building!
Episodes.Plot: It's going to be the best doghouse EVER! But before Bubble Puppy can move into his new doggy digs the Bubble Guppies have to build it. So put on your hard hat and roll up your sleeves; construction is about to begin.

Episodes.Title: Ducks in a Row!
Episodes.Plot: Duck! Nonny meets a Marching Band with a Duck problem. The Duck is in the way and they can't play their instruments! But with a little whistle, and a little help from Mr. Grouper and the Bubble Guppies, Nonny learns how to lead the Marching Band--ducks or no ducks.

Episodes.Title: The Grumpfish Special!
Episodes.Plot: At the Bubble Guppies restaurant you'll get a picture on your pizza and a smile on your face, unless of course you're the Grumpfish. From waiting tables to cooking food, the Bubble Guppies prepare to serve their most difficult customer yet. But is there anything on the menu that can get the Grumpfish grinning?

Episodes.Title: The Moon Rocks!
Episodes.Plot: Have you ever seen the moon in the daytime? Have you ever noticed it kinda looks like a big pizza? The Guppies have! Blast off and leave your home planet behind--it's time to check out the solar system with the Bubble Guppies!

Episodes.Title: Who's Gonna Play the Big Bad Wolf?
Episodes.Plot: Set the stage and light the lights! The Bubble Guppies are learning about plays! They're going to see the all-starfish production of "The Three Little Pigs." But when one of the actors can't perform, it's up to Deema to put on the costume and take the stage. It's show time!

Episodes.Title: We Totally Rock!
Episodes.Plot: Are you ready to rock? The Bubble Guppies are taking the stage with their guitars, drums and keyboards. Get ready to crank it up to 10 and learn about everything rock and roll.

Episodes.Title: Fishketball!
Episodes.Plot: The Bubble Guppies explore different kinds of ball games as they get ready for their big game of Fishketball! Join Team Guppies to help them practice bouncing, throwing, catching and playing together as a team.

Episodes.Title: The Legend of Pinkfoot
Episodes.Plot: The Bubble Guppies are going on a camping trip! Grab your flashlights and gather around the campfire to make s'mores and hear about the spooky legend of Pinkfoot!

Episodes.Title: Gup, Gup and Away!
Episodes.Plot: Pack a suitcase and hurry to the airport! Help the Bubble Guppies fly an airplane through the sky and over the clouds-just be sure to keep an eye out for airplane pirates!

Episodes.Title: The Spring Chicken is Coming!
Episodes.Plot: The Guppies have to plant a flower for the Spring Chicken.

Episodes.Title: Boy Meets Squirrel
Episodes.Plot: A squirrel named Doug gives Nonny an acorn, making Nonny wonder if it can become an acorn tree. But the Guppies have to learn about trees (and recycling) first!

Episodes.Title: Have A Cow!
Episodes.Plot:
A mother cow named Butterscotch is about to give birth to a new baby.

Note: This is the Mother's Day special. Mr. Grouper sing the pop song instead of Molly or Gil.

Songs: "The Farmer's Song", "Milk the Cow"

Shop: Animal Caller

Lunch Joke: Cheese and tractors

Storybook: "The Farmer and the Farmhand"
Field Trip: The farm.

Episodes.Title: Super Shrimptennial Celebration!
Episodes.Plot: The kids head to a huge bash their town is hosting at the top of Big Bubble Building.

Episodes.Title: Happy Clam Day!
Episodes.Plot: The kids learn about mail before sending out an invitation to a party for Clam.

Episodes.Title: Can You Dig It?
Episodes.Plot: The kids go to a dinosaur dig site, where they ask questions about the prehistoric creatures.

Episodes.Title: Bubble Bites
Episodes.Plot: The Bubble Guppies head to the supermarket to shop for fruits, vegetables and a box of Bubble Bites for Bubble Puppy.

Episodes.Title: Haunted House Party
Episodes.Plot: The Bubble Guppies are invited to a costume party at a haunted house.
